news.title: Registration of residential sales in Kolkata dips 15% year-on-year in August 2022
news.para: In all, 6,238 residential properties were registered in Kolkata Metropolitan Area in August 2022, down from 6,709 in July 2022. In August 2021 that had witnessed record registrations, the figure was 7,316.

news.title: TCP act amendments scrapped along with clearances under section 16B: Goa minister
news.para: State Town and Country Planning Minister Vishwajit Rane said the amendments were being scrapped as even keeping them in abeyance would have caused more doubts among people on the intention of the government.

news.title: Houses in Raipur to have digital door numbers, unique IDs
news.para: With the installation of digital door numbers on all 3.15 lakh houses in the city, the landlord will get 26 types of essential and emergency services, including payment of various taxes, door-to-door garbage collection and tap connection, conveniently sitting at home.

news.title: Vadodara: Housing project under PMAY to start after five years
news.para: The civic body had razed the dwellings and the shops in July 2017 in Sahakarnagar promising houses under a scheme on the same land for urban poor.

news.title: Survey of illegal structures in forest areas of four villages of Faridabad begins
news.para: ​​Provisions of the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980, would be applicable in these areas, the court had said. Some of the villages where land is notified under the PLPA are Ankhir, Mewla Maharajpur, Anangpur and Lakkarpur.

news.title: Supertech Emerald Court RWA raises dust concern
news.para: The process to transport debris to the construction and demolition waste plant in Sector 80 began on September 11, but only 200 tonnes of rubble had been removed, they said.

news.title: Cement companies' profitability to dip by 15% on rising input costs: Report
news.para: On credit profile, the report, based on an analysis of 22 cement-makers that account for 85 per cent of the market volume, said higher demand will mitigate the impact of lower profitability on absolute operating profit and cash accruals of cement makers.

news.title: GNIDA issues notice to Assotech Springfield's builder, AoA over parking wall collapse
news.para: ​The structural audit has to be conducted by an IIT or an equivalent institution as third party, the Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) said as it issued notice to the project's builder and the apartment owners' association (AoA).

news.title: IDFC First Bank leases 18 floors of office space from Hiranandani in Thane
news.para: This is one of the largest office lease transactions concluded this year. The private-sector bank will be paying Rs 202.5 crore as rental for the office space over the first five-year tenure of the lease, including maintenance.

news.title: In China, home buyers occupy their 'rotting', unfinished properties
news.para: Shanghai E-House Real Estate Research Institute estimated in July that stalled projects accounted for 3.85% of China's housing market in the first half of 2022, equivalent to an area of 231 million square metres.

news.title: Jaipur metro line-2 delay can escalate project cost
news.para: Officials said as per the initial Detailed Project Report (DPR), the cost for Line-2 was almost Rs 10,000 crore. Since the government was reluctant to spend such a huge amount, Metro officials prepared another DPR in 2021 in which the project cost came down to around Rs 4,600 crore.

news.title: About 7,700 homes flooded, Bengaluru civic body puts overall loss at Rs 340 crore
news.para: No less than 7,700 houses were inundated and 170 houses partially damaged during the recent floods that wreaked havoc in Bengaluru’s tech corridor, according to data provided by Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike.

news.title: Nagpur improvement trust hikes amalgamation charges of its leased plots
news.para: The proposal was to recover 2% of ready reckoner value, which would have been many times higher compared to the existing charges of Rs10,000.

news.title: Ministry of home affairs seeks property details from Chandigarh administration
news.para: Following a MHA letter received last week, the administration has issued directions to the estate office, Chandigarh Housing Board and municipal corporation, to prepare data.

news.title: Kanpur locals won't get inflated house tax bills: Mayor
news.para: House tax was one of the key issues to be discussed as corporators said that house owners were receiving exaggerated house tax bills due to a geographical survey being conducted by a Lucknow based company.
